=Li Zehou 李澤厚 (1930- )=
==Works==
===Bibliography===
* Heinrich Geiger: Chinesische Ästhetik im zwanzigsten Jahrhundert. Bibliographie: Zhu Guangqian (1897-1986), Zong Baihua (geb.1897) und Li Zehou (geb.1930). Berlin: C.Bell, 1987 
===Articles (western)===
* Li Zehou and Vera Schwarcz: Six Generations of Modern Chinese Intellectuals. Chinese Studies in History Vol. 15, No. 3-4 (1982)
* The Philosophy of Kant and a Theory Subjectivity. Analecta Husserliana, Vol. 21 (1986)
* Reading Notes on the Aesthetics of Zhuang Zi. Contemporary Chinese Thought 20/1 (1988):3-42.
* Chinas Aufklärung - Weg und Ziel: Entwurf für eine Rede zur Siebzigjahrfeier des 4. Mai. In Karl-Heinz Pohl u.a. [eds.]: Chinesische Intellektuelle im 20. Jahrhundert: Zwischen Tradition und Moderne. Hamburg: Institut für Asienkunde, 1993: 29-36.
* Contemporary Chinese Thought 31/2 (1999): 
> * A Few Questions Concerning the History of Chinese Aesthetics (Excerpts). Contemporary Chinese Thought 31 (2):66-76.
> * Some Tentative Remarks on China's Wisdom (Excerpts). Contemporary Chinese Thought 31 (2):44-65.
> * The Dual Variation of Enlightenment and Nationalism: (Excerpt). Contemporary Chinese Thought 31 (2):40-43.
> * The Image Level and Artistic Sedimentation (Excerpts). Contemporary Chinese Thought 31 (2):77-88.
> * An Outline of the Origin of Humankind. Contemporary Chinese Thought 31 (2):20-25.
> * A Supplementary Explanation of Subjectivity. Contemporary Chinese Thought 31 (2):26-31.
> * The Western Is the Substance, and the Chinese Is for Application: (Excerpts). Contemporary Chinese Thought 31 (2):32-39.
> * Mourning professor Feng Youlan by engaging in serious philosophical discussion today. Journal of Chinese Philosophy 21 (3-4):471-480.
> * Subjectivity and "subjectality": A response. Philosophy East and West 49 (2):174-183.

